<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-101-670  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 101 670.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Jan 30 1990 v4 n4 p3(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mitem/Tri-Data link for host apps. (Mitem Corp enhances MitemViewinterface software to take advantage of IBM 3270 applicationprogramming interface) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Garner, Rachelle.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mitem Corp. (products)Tri-Data Systems Inc. (products).andO;Product:   MitemView (Program development software) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Communications Boards-CardsGateways (Interface)Network ManagementMicro-Mainframe CommunicationEnhancementsSoftware PackagesProgram Development ToolsProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Rochelle GarnerandM;Santa Clara, Calif.andP;  -- Managers who want to make mainframe applicationsaccessible and friendly to Mac users without modifying host code can nowcombine MitemView, Mitem Corp.'s HyperCard-based interface software, withTri-Data Systems Inc.'s Netway Systems Network Architecture (SNA) gateways.andM;The companies announced here last week that MitemView now takes advantage ofTri-Data's 3270 application programming interface (API) to support multiplehost sessions and communications with multiple hosts.andP;  The Netway APIprovides the procedural calls needed to establish 3270 sessions, manipulateon-screen data and transmit mainframe screens.andM;MitemView lets in-house developers create simple graphical interfaces forhost applications.andP;  Tri-Data's Netway gateways function as 3174 clustercontrollers on an SNA network, eliminating the need for token-ring, Ethernetor 3270 coaxial cards in each Mac.andP;  One Mac can serve as a gateway linking aLocalTalk LAN to the host.andM;The MitemView developers toolkit is priced at $995.andP;  The module with the 3270API, necessary for MitemView and Netway gateways to work together, costs$495.andP;  Both are available from Mitem.andM;Mitem Corp. is located at 2105 Hamilton Ave., Suite 190, San Jose, Calif.andO;95125; (408) 559-8801.andM;Tri-Data Systems Inc. moved last month to a new location at 3270 Scott Blvd.,andO;Santa Clara, Calif.andP;  95054; (408) 727-3270.andO;</TEXT></DOC>